>  minutes later, my tank is overflowing with gas at even the SLIGHTEST
>  incline.  Sometimes without an incline!  I cant figure out why changing
>  the sender (from a non-cylindrical to a non-cylindrical) would change
>  things in my tank so that this will happen?  Does this happen to many
